      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modelled QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution) must directly address the decision question of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index derived from power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger model is the regulatory-accepted QoI for CPB hemolysis risk. Shear stress distributions support mechanistic interpretation. Both QoIs directly inform the worst-case operating condition identification decision."
