      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid analogue, and operating envelope as the intended clinical CPB application.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump with glycerol-water blood analogue at clinically representative flow rates (3–7 L/min) and rotational speeds (2500–5500 RPM), directly spanning the CPB operating envelope."
